subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
Forewing length 6.5–7.0 mm (n=4). Head black (
Fig. 3a
), slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes dark brown; antennae (
Fig. 7b
) dark brown, inner margin with long hairs. Pronotum (
Fig. 3a
) brown, surface with dark brown longitudinal median and paramedial elliptical rugosities, anterior corners rounded, posterior corners angulate; wings subhyaline, veins brown; legs brown. Abdomen brown, terminalia mostly dark brown.
